Warner Sugar Refining Company, Libelant-Appellee, v. THE Steamship S. V. HARKNESS, Her Engines, etc.; Standard Oil Company (N. J.), Claimant-Appellant. No. 206. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 17, 1930. Kirlin, Campbell, Hiekox, Keating & MeGrann, of New York City (J. Harvey Turnure, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City (Leonard J. Matteson and Richard F. Shaw, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
